# Claude Code Rules — CHI NLP Pipeline

## Cost Guard (CRITICAL)

Before ANY scoring run, calculate estimated cost:
  Formula: (n_traditions × 10 × 20 × 700 × $3/MTok input) + (n_traditions × 10 × 20 × 100 × $15/MTok output)
  Quick: ~$0.72 per tradition

If estimated cost > $15 USD: STOP and ask for confirmation before proceeding.
Display as: "Estimated cost: ~$X.XX for N traditions. Proceed? [y/n]"

Use `python tasks.py cost-estimate` or `python tasks.py cost-estimate --traditions X Y`

Log actual token usage after each scoring run to output/cost_log.json if possible.

## Never Without Explicit Confirmation

- `python src/main.py --stage score` (bare, all traditions) without cost check
- Any destructive data/ operation (deleting embeddings, raw corpus files)
- Re-embed while another scoring process is running (will corrupt results)
- Pushing to remote (user will create the remote themselves)

## Corpus Workflow — Always Follow This Order

When adding or changing any tradition:
  1. Add to config/pipeline_config.yaml
  2. Add keywords to src/corpus/keywords.py
  3. python tasks.py corpus <tradition>
  4. python tasks.py validate-corpus          ← NEVER SKIP THIS
  5. python tasks.py embed                    ← full index rebuild, all traditions
  6. python tasks.py score <tradition>        ← NOT score-all unless corpus changed for all
  7. python tasks.py export

## Scoring Rules

- Always use --tradition flag for incremental runs: `python tasks.py score norse shinto`
- NEVER run score-all unless ALL corpus files have been validated since the last embed
- Never run score immediately after changing corpus — always embed first
- Check file timestamps: `ls -la data/embeddings/corpus.index data/processed/scoring_results.json`
  If scoring_results.json is older than corpus.index, re-score

## PG ID Verification (prevents the #1 recurring bug)

BEFORE adding any Project Gutenberg source to config:
  1. Fetch https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/NNNN and read the title
  2. Confirm title matches expected text
  3. Test the .txt URL: try /cache/epub/NNNN/pgNNNN.txt first, then /files/NNNN/NNNN-0.txt
  4. Add source URL only after confirming both title AND URL work

NEVER guess PG IDs. Wrong IDs have caused 7 mismatches in production (see docs/RUNBOOK.md).

## API Key Security

API key location: C:\Users\secki\OneDrive\Desktop\claude_code_standalone_exercises\api_keys_seckin\config.py
Contains: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY variable — NEVER log, print, or commit its value.

## Corpus Validation

After any corpus download, run `python tasks.py validate-corpus`.
A SUSPICIOUS result means the downloaded text doesn't contain tradition keywords.
Do NOT embed suspicious files — fix the source URL first.

## min_relevance_threshold by Text Type

- Doctrinal texts (sutras, upanishads, gita): 0.3
- Mythological prose (eddas, theogony, popol vuh): 0.2
- Poetic/verse (vedic hymns, lyric poetry): 0.15

Current pipeline default: 0.2 (in config/pipeline_config.yaml)

## Parallelization

Fan out parallel agents for independent tasks:
- Downloading multiple corpus sources
- Scoring different traditions (they do NOT share state)
- Generating docs files
- Validating corpus for different traditions

Sequential dependencies that CANNOT be parallelized:
  corpus → validate → embed → score → export

## Large Files Stay Out of Git

Excluded by .gitignore:
- data/raw/         (downloaded corpus, regenerable)
- data/embeddings/  (FAISS index, regenerable from corpus)
- data/processed/   (intermediate results, regenerable)
- .venv/

Kept in git:
- output/chi_dataset_grounded.json
- output/evidence_document.md
- data/cosmologies_v1_manual.json

## Index Lifecycle

The FAISS index covers ALL traditions in a single file.
Adding or changing ANY tradition's corpus requires full re-embed of all traditions.
After re-embed: index size should change (check with `python -c "import faiss; print(faiss.read_index('data/embeddings/corpus.index').ntotal)"`)
